It's not big and fancy but located next door to a dog park so we enjoyed watching all the dogs being walked in the area. You could tell it was a neighborhood hangout and they support the local sports team.  We went in around 3pm on a Monday afternoon. The entire place was very quiet and there were not many people in the restaurant. My husband ordered the mild chicken wings. They came out well cooked and the sauce was good. His feedback was the sauce had more heat to it then they server let on to so he wished she would have been a little more clear on the heat level and that the celery on the plate look like it has been cut into three pieces from a normal cut in order to save a few bucks.  My mother ordered the blackened chicken sandwich with fries. She enjoyed it very much.  I ordered the DT nachos. Love the flavor overall but I wish the nachos were layered - all of the toppings were on top so after eating the top layer - it was just chips underneath. I also think the onion needs to be diced - the chunks were just a bit much given the lack of layering.

We ordered from District Tavern off of Uber Eats as they were one of the only restaurants open late and I'm SO glad we did. We decided to order a few appetizers to split.  Tavern Shooters: 3/5. I thought this was going to be my favorite item, but it was my least favorite. I will say the tomato soup was very good, but the grilled cheeses had almost no flavor and were not cheesy or crispy as expected. Also, the bread ratio was totally off. Skip these.  Mozzarella Balls: 4/5. Very solid take on mozzarella sticks. The insides were actually very soft and not as crunchy as a traditional mozzarella stick is, so I really enjoyed them.  Washington Park Pretzel: 4/5. What can I say, I love a good pretzel. Anytime a pretzel is on the menu, you can bet I'm ordering it. The pretzel was very good, not as great as WOB's but a very solid choice. The cheese dip was delicious, however the mustard was way too overpowering and strong on the pretzel.  Beer Battered Onion Rings: 5/5. I am actually surprised that this was our favorite item we ordered. The batter on the onion rings was ridiculously light and fluffy but still so crunchy at the same time. I'd order these again and again.  Fredo Flatbread: 4/5. The flatbread was perfectly crispy and had a great combination of flavors between the spinach, bacon, and Alfredo sauce. My only complaint is that I wish it had more bacon, I couldn't stop gobbling it up. You can add chicken to this as well.  Overall, we really enjoyed our meal. They're not in the best location, but if I'm ever over in Channelside I'd definitely stop in!

Shame on you!
